ent, and course completion rates. Institutions failing to meet these benchmarks risk recruitment restrictions or losing sponsorship licenses, aiming to ensure genuine study purposes.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-tightens-student-visa-rules-as-universities-face-ban-over-international-student-visa-abuse/articleshow/131526050.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-tightens-student-visa-rules-as-universities-face-ban-over-international-student-visa-abuse/articleshow/131526050.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-05T13:54:49+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131526209,imgsize-26018.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['In best of families...': Netanyahu responds to Trump's 'crazy' remark, acknowledges 'tactical disagreements']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131523079.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu acknowledged 'tactical disagreements' with US President Trump over regional conflicts but emphasized their shared goals, particularly countering Iran's nuclear ambitions and Hezbollah. Despite recent heated exchanges, Netanyahu hailed Trump as Israel's 'greatest friend,' citing his strong support for the nation. Both leaders aim for regional stability.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/in-best-of-families-netanyahu-responds-to-trumps-crazy-remark-acknowledges-tactical-disagreements/articleshow/131523079.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/in-best-of-families-netanyahu-responds-to-trumps-crazy-remark-acknowledges-tactical-disagreements/articleshow/131523079.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-05T11:46:07+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc